      • AverageReadyCount

        static final String AverageReadyCount
        The #of tasks that are waiting to run on the internal lock used by the WriteExecutorService to coordinate the start and end of tasks and the group commit. This counter indicates how much potential concurrency is being wasted by the WriteExecutorService.

      • AverageByteCountPerCommit

        static final String AverageByteCountPerCommit
        Moving average of the #of bytes written since the previous commit (zero unless the service is unisolated).

        Note: This DOES NOT imply that this many bytes were written in the commit itself. Indices are checkpointed after each task. All writes on the journal should have already occurred before the group commit. The commit protocol itself involves writing a very few bytes and then syncing the disk.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        The #of commits (only reported services which do commit processing).

        The #of aborts (only reported services which do commit processing).
        See Also:

      • OverflowCount

        static final String OverflowCount
        The #of synchronous overflow events (only reported services which do commit processing). A synchronous overflow event is when the index partitions on the live journal are re-defined onto a new live journal. Asynchronous overflow processing then proceeds in the background handling index partition builds, splits, joins, moves, etc.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • RejectedExecutionCount

        static final String RejectedExecutionCount
        The #of tasks whose execution was rejected, typically because the queue was at capacity.

      • AverageCommitGroupSize

        static final String AverageCommitGroupSize
        Moving average of the #of tasks that participate in commit group. (The size of the most recent commit group is sampled and turned into a moving average.)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        static final String MaxCommitGroupSize

        See Also:

      • MaxRunning

        static final String MaxRunning
        The maximum #of tasks that are concurrently executing without regard to whether or not the tasks have acquired their locks.

        Note: Since this does not reflect tasks executing concurrently with locks held it is not a measure of the true concurrency of tasks executing on the service.
